remarks: St. Joseph's Convent Teachers' Training Institute is situated in the lush green  area of Belgavi city in North Karnataka region.  It is the only one English medium  Training college in this region.  It was established in the year 1946 by the Cannossian sisters and is run by St.Joseph's society, Belgavi.  It has received its permanent recognition in the year 1975.  The course is conducted in a beautiful and well constructed building.  The Management has provided all the facilities for the staff and students.  We have a well equipped laboratory, a spacious library, computer and Psycho Lab. and specious class rooms and well qualified staff.  Almost al the year we do have cent percentage results and al of them secure jobs immediately after their exams, in different schools of Karnataka.  Quite many of them have secured government jobs and are spread far and wide not only in India but even abroad.  The trainees are given all round formation. We try to inculcate sound human values and enable them to discover their various hidden talents and help the to put out their full potential, by proving them various opportunities.  Thus we try to have a balanced bend of academics, teaching skills, co curricular activities, sports etc. and nurture them to bloom into a multi talented and progressive teachers of 21st century.  In this modern world of technologies we train them to use various modern methods of teaching thus to be effective in their profession.   We do adapt   our training programmes as per the guidelines given by the department every year so that the trainees are kept abreast with the modern methods of teaching and evaluation.   The trainees are guided and trained to undertake action research and other activities during their training period.

remarks: Sevamandir - The Temple of Service outwardly a silent school and home with openness and joy is situated just outside Portonovo, Parangipettai, the recent name, is situated between Chidambaram and Cuddalore.Annie Marie Petersen of Denmark, a rare lover of humanity, founded the institution. Her love and devotion for India captured the heart of Mahatma Gandhi. In 1921, Sep 18th, Gandhiji laid the foundation stone and he gave the name it bears today. The motto of the institution is "Love and Serve".At first, it was started with three children. Now it has grown with more than 2000 children every year. It is a composite institute with many other schools. All the children are residing in our hostel.In 1949, Sevamandir was recognized as Junior Basic Training School for women.  In 1956, the Junior basic school was converted in to  a senior Basic Training school.1949 onwards, it is producing many efficient and dynamic teachers who are in the different parts of the world.Sevamandir will continue its service for the upliftment of the poor, specially, for the females and for the benefits of the society.

remarks: Our academic efforts are focused on achieving 100% gainful placement genuinely.  We have 35 years of fabulous links with the reputed industries throughout the country.  Our Diploma programmes are very well recognised in the industry with full appreciation for the professional skills of our Alumni.  Cordial and mutually beneficial industry-Institute Interaction for promoting employment opportunities and inplant training for our students are the inherent features of our Placement & Training Cell.  Hence, the purpose of educating the students and assuring the benefits of fruitful career are accomplished with a great drive and enthusiasm by all the departments of our College.Our Alumni Association with a membership of 8450 is among the pillars of our Institution. It conducts the Annual General Body Meeting every year on 1st of May without fail for the past 17 years. Community Development Through Polytechnic (CDTP) scheme sponsored by the Ministry of Human Resources Development (MHRD),  Government of India has been implemented successfully to provide skill oriented training to rural community in our region at free of cost. Eight extensions centres are functioning in the nearby rural areas to offer need based training and transfer of technology. A contingent of National Cadet Corps (NCC) is functioning robustly to mould our students into responsible citizens and develop the leadership qualities with respect for duty and discipline. Two units of National Service Scheme (NSS) which have been sanctioned by the Directorate of Technical Education are periodically organising  special projects  to train the students in individual, institutional and Community Development Programmes. Apex Club, Apex Ladies Club, Rotract Club, Youth Red Cross and Red Ribbon Club are contributing in the arena of personality and character development. The Directorate of Technical Education initiated CIICP Project offers short term vocational courses lasting 3 to 6 months duration as part time program

remarks: ABOUNT THE MANAGEMENTIn 1844 Puducherry during a diocession synod the president Mgr.Clement Bonane, Vicar Apostolic of Puducherry spoke emphatically in the necessity of wmen education. The synod's priests proposed the idea that an Indian sisters congregation should be started and the sisters should be entrusted with the respondibility of teaching, together with secular education and moral education.In this situation impelled by the pastoral charity of Christ the teacher par excellence Rev.Fr. Louis Savenien Dupuis came forward to execute this plan and visioned for the liberation of women which could be achieved only through the education of women. The management's educational services have been spread to all over India, Paua New Guinea, Africa, America and italy. So many Primary, High, Higher Secondary Schools, Colleges, Community College, engineering College were established and run by our congregation effectively throughout India, Africa, Australia and America.In mid 19th century, the church in Tamilnadu began to realize the absolute need of women education. The yearning desire of the founders of Sacred Heart Teacher Training Institute, Cuddalore liberating women through education and helping them to be self reliant. Empowering women through education is the only way of women's liberation. If paves the way of self reliance and preserves the dignity of womanhood.The Institute was founded in 1934 and the aim of the institute is giving preference to the poor and marginalized women and thus creating a new society. For the past 81 years, the institute has framed more than a lakh of comitted and dynamic teachers who brings out the noblest element in all children of God especially the girls in order to have the Dharshan of God illuminated with wisdom, in this century. The institute is situated in a beautiful background on the main road, ECR, Chennai. The institute has got sufficient infrastructures and instructional facilities.
